 Five fresh
cases of coronavirus have been confirmed by the NCDC Saturday night. According to tweets by NCDC, out of  five new cases, 3 were reported in Bauchi while the FCT recorded two. NCDC said, “Five new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria: 3 in Bauchi and 2 in the FCT. “As at 10:10 pm 4th April there are 214 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Twenty-five have been discharged with four deaths. Five new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria: 3 in Bauchi and 2 in the FCT.As at 10:10 pm 4th April there are 214 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Twenty-five have been discharged with four deaths pic.twitter.com/NDz5FFMrdF